ators.js","line":738,"details":"createExternalIntegrationsICp680CoverageSummary returns `pack_id: EXTERNAL_INTEGRATIONS_I_CP679_PACK_BINDING.pack_id` ('CP00-679') instead of EXTERNAL_INTEGRATIONS_I_CP680_PACK_BINDING.pack_id ('CP00-680'). The sibling summaries each correctly reference their own binding (CP678 at validators.js:683 -> CP678; CP679 at validators.js:713 -> CP679), confirming this is a copy-paste oversight in the new CP680 deliverable. Impact is latent and non-blocking: validateExternalIntegrationsICp680Coverage (validators.js:741) does not check the summary's pack_id; the validator script (scripts/validate-rp22-external-integrations-i-contract.mjs:249-250,425) only asserts coverage.valid and logs unit_count; the CP680 coverage test (packages/integrations-core/test/model.test.js:386-396) asserts first_unit_id, last_unit_id, unit_count, and by_* distributions but never summary.pack_id; and the coverage summary is not embedded in either contract projection. Consequently all 22 reported validation commands still pass and no boundary, no-real-data, authority, or production_ready gate is affected. The defect is confined to an objectively incorrect pack_id label emitted by an exported helper.","recommendation":"Change validators.js:738 to reference EXTERNAL_INTEGRATIONS_I_CP680_PACK_BINDING.pack_id, and consider adding `assert.equal(coverage.summary.pack_id, 'CP00-680')` to the CP00-680 coverage test to prevent recurrence. Safe to fix in a follow-up touch (e.g., during CP00-681); does not block CP00-680 descriptor-only closeout.","post_review_disposition":"Open, non-blocking P2. Referred to implementer; recommend correcting validators.js:738 and adding a summary.pack_id assertion in a follow-up. Does not gate CP00-680 closeout (verdict PASS_WITH_FINDINGS, no_unresolved_p0/p1=true)."}],"finding_counts":{"p0":0,"p1":0,"p2":1,"p3":0,"reported_p0":0,"reported_p1":0,"reported_p2":1,"reported_p3":0}},"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"8994